    "comment": "Rationale: \"we stained cultured hippocampal neurons with antibodies directed against SENP7, MAP2, and the synaptic markers drebrin and synaptophysin. We acquired images using both confocal microscopy with a 40× objective (Figure 3A,G) and 3D-SIM microscopy (Figure 3B,C,H,I and Supplemental Figure S3A,B).\n\nSimilarly to SENP1 and SENP6, we found that SENP7 is both a nuclear and cytoplasmic protein. Outside the nucleus, it partially colocalizes with synaptic markers, as indicated by Mander's and Pearson's correlation coefficients (Figure 3D-F,J-L).\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Primary hippocampal neurons were prepared as previously described by Colnaghi et al., 2019 [36]. Briefly, the dissected hippocampi were obtained from two-day-old CD1 mice.\"\n\nantibodies:\nSENP1 (C-12, Santa Cruz, sc-271360)\nSENP6 (79-M, Santa Cruz, sc-100585)\nSENP7 (E-8, Santa Cruz, sc-373821)\nmicrotubule-associated protein 2 (Map2) (Abcam, AB5392)\nsynaptophysin (Synaptic System, GmbH101002)\ndrebrin (Vinci-Biochem, BSR-M05530)",
